ensive history of the Barbie trial, including the investigation leading up to it, the legal background to the case, and the hurdles the prosecution had to clear in order to bring Barbie to justice. Richard J. Golsan examines the strategies used by the defence, the prosecution, and the lawyers who represented Barbie’s many victims at the trial. The book draws from press coverage, articles, and books about Barbie and the trial published at the time, as well as recently released archival sources and the personal archives of lawyers at the trial. Making the case that, despite the views of its many critics, the Barbie trial was a success in legal, historical, and pedagogical terms, Justice in Lyon details how the trial has had a positive impact on French and international law governing crimes against humanity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aCrimes against humanityzFrancezLyon. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zFrance. 0aWar crime trialszFrancezLyon. 0aWar crimes investigationzFrancezLyon. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocitieszFrancezLyon. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszFrancezLyon. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aFrance.  aGermany.  aHolocaust.  aKlaus Barbie.  aLyon.  aNazi hunters.  aNazism.  aOccupation.  aWWII.  aWorld War Two.  acrimes against humanity.  agenocide.  ahistoric trials.  ainternational law.  alegal history.  awar crimes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753416540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487534165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487534165/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles